  "description": "Bengt Folke Jakobsson was a Swedish engineer born on January 5, 1916 in Gothenburg. He passed his high school exams at Gothenburg's Upper Secondary School in 1934, and received his Masters in Engineering from Chalmers University of Technology in 1937 with a focus on mechanical engineering. He was employed by SKF in Gothenburg in 1938, and then worked at Åtvidaberg Industries in Åtvidaberg from 1939 to 1941, before working as a teacher at Chalmers and Gothenburg's Technical High School from 1941 to 1943. From 1944 onwards, he was a design engineer for Swedish Aero Engines Ltd, Trollhättan division, located in Gothenburg. He wrote a dissertation titled 'Steering of Tracked Vehicles' in 1947."
